section.para:
Assuming that



      You created a Linux virtual machine using the <ProjectName>-lan network;



      Your VM got the 10.64.15.3 IP address; The VM is CentOS based so there is a default user called 'centos';



      You stored your my_key keypair in ~/private on the gate machine;



you can access your VM from the gate machine issuing


$ ssh -i ~/private/my_key centos@10.64.15.3

If needed, e.g. if a VM should host a service accessible from the Internet, such VM on the Cloud can be given a public IP. For this purpose you will need:
to instantiate the VM on the <ProjectName>-wan network;
to allocate a floating (public) IP to the VM, as discussed in .

listitem.para:
Shutdown your VM:
	Log in as root to your VM. Please DO NOT shutdown the VM from the Openstack dashboard
    to make sure all data are correctly flushed on disk;
